    <summary>Topographic openness expresses the dominance (positive) or enclosure (negative) of a landscape location. See Yokoyama et al. (2002) for a precise definition. Openness has been related to how wide a landscape can be viewed from any position. It has been proven to be a meaningful input for computer aided geomorphological mapping. </summary>
